So use the APIs Explorer to get
the information about a

00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:38.190
specific activity, given
the activity ID.

00:12:38.190 --> 00:12:41.840
And that specific activity
had a document shared.

00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:44.100
And so this is a request.

00:12:44.100 --> 00:12:46.420
If you know the Google+ API,
this is very easy to

00:12:46.420 --> 00:12:46.910
understand.

00:12:46.910 --> 00:12:48.910
We just do a get to
the specific end

00:12:48.910 --> 00:12:50.240
point for the activity.

00:12:50.240 --> 00:12:53.130
And we get some metadata here.

00:12:53.130 --> 00:12:55.560
But what?

00:12:55.560 --> 00:13:00.220
We don't see a reference
to the document itself.

00:13:00.220 --> 00:13:04.510
So do you want to just explain
a bit what we see here?

00:13:04.510 --> 00:13:04.930
GUS CLASS: Sure.

00:13:04.930 --> 00:13:08.180
So some of the things that
you're seeing currently is the

00:13:08.180 --> 00:13:11.410
format of these activities is
that there's the activity

00:13:11.410 --> 00:13:14.280
itself, an actor associated with
the activity, and then

00:13:14.280 --> 00:13:18.620
attachments that are appended
onto the end of that activity.

00:13:18.620 --> 00:13:22.520
And so the attachment of
interest is going to be the

00:13:22.520 --> 00:13:26.330
actual share that happened
from that Drive post.

00:13:26.330 --> 00:13:33.310
And so if you look into the
object array that's specified

00:13:33.310 --> 00:13:38.640
in the JSON at the end of this
content here, the first one

00:13:38.640 --> 00:13:39.700
will actually be something that

00:13:39.700 --> 00:13:42.650
represents the post itself.

00:13:42.650 --> 00:13:46.430
And currently, we're sending
back a self link so that if

00:13:46.430 --> 00:13:49.480
you were using this inside of
a third party integration,

00:13:49.480 --> 00:13:51.850
where you're reading this
activity content, you could

00:13:51.850 --> 00:13:53.410
link back to the post
really easily.

00:13:56.890 --> 00:14:01.060
What is interesting to me is
actually getting back to that

00:14:01.060 --> 00:14:02.590
base URL from Drive.

00:14:02.590 --> 00:14:06.020
Because then once you can
do that, you can start

00:14:06.020 --> 00:14:11.030
incorporating the Drive API to
get the one true metadata from

00:14:11.030 --> 00:14:13.140
the actual object
itself in Drive.

00:14:13.140 --> 00:14:16.430
CLAUDIO CHERUBINO: That's an
important point to highlight.

00:14:16.430 --> 00:14:19.050
So this integration
is totally new.

00:14:19.050 --> 00:14:22.390
So we are still working on
it and we appreciate your

00:14:22.390 --> 00:14:23.420
feedback on it.

00:14:23.420 --> 00:14:27.560
And at the moment, the Google+
API doesn't expose any

00:14:27.560 --> 00:14:30.520
information about the
shared document.

00:14:30.520 --> 00:14:32.910
But we think it might be
worth considering this

00:14:32.910 --> 00:14:33.780
addition to the API.

00:14:33.780 --> 00:14:37.740
So we will bring this
up and see if we can

00:14:37.740 --> 00:14:39.540
add it to the API.

00:14:39.540 --> 00:14:44.650
But assuming we get a reference
to the document in

00:14:44.650 --> 00:14:48.560
the API, what we would expect
is to only get an ID or a

00:14:48.560 --> 00:14:50.810
reference to the document,
but nothing else.

00:14:50.810 --> 00:14:53.830
Well, maybe the title or the
rest of the metadata that are

00:14:53.830 --> 00:14:55.100
in the snippet.

00:14:55.100 --> 00:14:56.440
But that's it.

00:14:56.440 --> 00:15:01.550
Then we would expect developers
to use that ID

00:15:01.550 --> 00:15:05.030
together with the Drive API to
perform activities, to perform

00:15:05.030 --> 00:15:08.150
actions on the document
itself.

00:15:08.150 --> 00:15:12.890
So if we add information about
a document to the Plus API,

00:15:12.890 --> 00:15:15.560
that information should only
be used together with the

00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:16.790
Drive API to perform

00:15:16.790 --> 00:15:18.270
manipulation of the file content.

00:15:18.270 --> 00:15:22.730
So don't expect, let's say,
the content of the

00:15:22.730 --> 00:15:24.690
presentation to be available
in the Plus API.

00:15:24.690 --> 00:15:27.970
There will be an overlap between
the Google+ API, the

00:15:27.970 --> 00:15:29.490
Google Doc, and Google
Drive API.

00:15:29.490 --> 00:15:33.100
And also remember that the
Google+ API asks for some

00:15:33.100 --> 00:15:36.350
specific permissions
that do not include

00:15:36.350 --> 00:15:37.630
reading your document.

00:15:37.630 --> 00:15:42.160
So if an application can only
read your Google+ API, it

00:15:42.160 --> 00:15:44.450
should not be allowed to
read your document.

00:15:44.450 --> 00:15:47.630
If you want to do both, you will
have to request for both

00:15:47.630 --> 00:15:50.650
permissions, and the
user will have to

00:15:50.650 --> 00:15:51.960
specifically approve both.

00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:52.590
Which makes sense.

00:15:52.590 --> 00:15:55.900
And it guarantees security and
privacy for your data.

00:15:55.900 --> 00:16:01.430
GUS CLASS: So yeah, like you
were saying, really having the

00:16:01.430 --> 00:16:04.230
document within Drive and then
making changes to that

00:16:04.230 --> 00:16:07.200
document also would then be
reflected in the content

00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:08.450
that's referenced.

00:16:10.740 --> 00:16:14.800
We want people to make all
of their reads from Drive

00:16:14.800 --> 00:16:16.340
documents as opposed
to directly

00:16:16.340 --> 00:16:17.480
through the Google+ API.

00:16:17.480 --> 00:16:19.560
You avoid duplication of data.

00:16:19.560 --> 00:16:23.020
And also, you kind of have
that definitive privacy

00:16:23.020 --> 00:16:26.200
control that happens
at the Drive side.

00:16:26.200 --> 00:16:27.450
CLAUDIO CHERUBINO: So we're
going to investigate this, and

00:16:27.450 --> 00:16:30.620
we're going to investigate
how to add these

00:16:30.620 --> 00:16:31.870
features to the API.

00:16:31.870 --> 00:16:34.340
And we might talk about this
in a future Google

00:16:34.340 --> 00:16:35.260
Developers Lab event.

00:16:35.260 --> 00:16:36.350
GUS CLASS: Yes, absolutely.

00:16:36.350 --> 00:16:36.650
CLAUDIO CHERUBINO: Cool.

