00:16:46.180 --> 00:16:50.510
But this integration works with
all types of documents on

00:16:50.510 --> 00:16:51.430
Google Drive.

00:16:51.430 --> 00:16:54.020
So you can share a text
document, you can share a

00:16:54.020 --> 00:16:56.520
spreadsheet, you can share a
presentation, and so on.

00:16:56.520 --> 00:17:00.570
So obviously, they will have
different renderings.

00:17:00.570 --> 00:17:02.650
So a presentation
looks like this.

00:17:02.650 --> 00:17:03.560
You can browse the slide.

00:17:03.560 --> 00:17:06.470
With a spreadsheet, it obviously
looks different.

00:17:06.470 --> 00:17:10.010
And each of them has
a specific UI.

00:17:10.010 --> 00:17:14.000
And the last thing I want to
mention is that we added this

00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:16.380
new feature for Google
properties right now.

00:17:16.380 --> 00:17:19.849
So you can share Google
Docs into Google+.

00:17:19.849 --> 00:17:23.430
But as we said, all it takes
for us to understand what a

00:17:23.430 --> 00:17:27.980
document is, is to add some
generic metadata coming from

00:17:27.980 --> 00:17:29.060
schema.org.

00:17:29.060 --> 00:17:34.720
And no one prevents other
products to do the same.

00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:38.590
So for instance, many of you
will know SlideShare.

00:17:38.590 --> 00:17:43.560
SlideShare is a very popular
service for hosting slides.

00:17:43.560 --> 00:17:46.790
Nothing prevents them from
adding those metadata.

00:17:46.790 --> 00:17:51.790
And we do not render that yet,
but we are definitely thinking

00:17:51.790 --> 00:17:53.990
about doing it for
other properties.

00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:57.790
So we need to balance between
avoiding spam

00:17:57.790 --> 00:17:58.520
and things like that.

00:17:58.520 --> 00:18:02.140
We don't want anyone to add
random data there, and we then

00:18:02.140 --> 00:18:06.960
have to be forced to capture
those data or do something to

00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:08.280
prevent abuse.

00:18:08.280 --> 00:18:12.810
But for instance, for important
third parties like

00:18:12.810 --> 00:18:17.410
SlideShare or others, we can
think about extending this new

00:18:17.410 --> 00:18:20.620
feature to support all
presentations out there, all

00:18:20.620 --> 00:18:22.760
documents out there,
and so on.

00:18:22.760 --> 00:18:23.140
GUS CLASS: Yep.

00:18:23.140 --> 00:18:25.910
Yeah, you highlighted
a really good point.

00:18:25.910 --> 00:18:30.340
With schema.org, when you have
your page marked up well,

00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:36.360
Google can do a lot more with
that content when they have

00:18:36.360 --> 00:18:39.930
those hints from within
your document as

00:18:39.930 --> 00:18:40.870
to what is in there.

00:18:40.870 --> 00:18:42.780
And so Google always tries
to calculate the

00:18:42.780 --> 00:18:44.240
right thing to render.

00:18:44.240 --> 00:18:46.275
And over time, these
things change.

